@saravanan.kesavan  Below are my finding.When a MongoDB timeout exception occurs, we handle the error in the CustomizedResponseEntityExceptionHandler class with method (handleAllExceptions) . Initially, we log the exception to New Relic, and then return an error response. The MessageResolverService is used to retrieve the ApiError object, where we invoke messageResolverService.getCode(message) and messageResolverService.getMessage(message), passing ex.getMessage() as a string parameter to both methods. During this process, the service attempts to load the properties file using MessageResolverService.loadProperties(). However, when calling Thread.currentThread().getContextClassLoader().getResourceAsStream(), it returns null, leading to a NullPointerException when attempting to load the properties.While checking more the reason might be the error message file is not created.Does Not Create Directories: The code does not create any directories. It only attempts to load a properties file from the classpath. If the file does not exist, getResourceAsStream will return null, and calling properties.load(inputStream) will throw a NullPointerException.", "mentions": []}]

