hi @Debadree Dutta ,The cashback offer was not applied due to several system failures during the transaction.Although the POS system was able to get the available offers, the process to apply the cashback did not complete because the system did not respond in time. At the same time, many server errors (5xx errors) occurred, indicating internal server problems.The failure started with an issue in generating a security token (an OAuth token) that the system needs to check and apply the offers. Without this token, the system could not verify if the offer should be applied. Additionally, an AWS server issue was identified where the database server had a problem and was automatically replaced. High CPU usage (99.5%) caused the database to restart, leading to further delays and failures.As a result, since the system could not verify the offer properly, the cashback offer was not applied. We can clearly see that the resource consumption was high and the CPU utilization reached around 99%, which resulted in response times of approximately 30 seconds and ultimately a timeout. Alerts were also generated for the same issue. CC @Suresh Moturi @Ayush Kumar Regards,Harshitha A", "mentions": []}]

