@Debadree Dutta , Analysis of OTA GetOffers and Transaction API Failure (March 2, 8:18 PM - 9:18 PM IST)The OTA GetOffers and Transaction APIs experienced failures during this period due to issues at the OAuth token generation phase, which temporarily failed but has since recovered.Root Cause Analysis:OAuth Token Request FailureThe failure occurred during the OAuth token generation phase, preventing API calls from proceeding.The OAuth request originated from Site24x7 at 8:40:29 PM IST.The request failed due to a connection timeout at intouch-api-v3-jsvt.High CPU Utilization Leading to Database Restart (Reason for timeouts)The database experienced 99.5% CPU utilization, causing it to restart.This was triggered by some applications consuming excessive resources during that period.A screenshot of the top resource-consuming users has been captured for reference.AWS Infrastructure Issue (Reason for db restart)AWS Support confirmed that the underlying EC2 machine for Aurora Compute encountered an issue.As a result, AWS's monitoring system automatically replaced the affected instance.AWS Support Case ID: 174108061100154.For this issue, alerts were triggered and you can refer the below tickets for the same :", "mentions": []}]

